org.foxlabs.validation

Class ConstrainedMap.Transaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.foxlabs.validation.ConstrainedMap.Transaction
  • Enclosing class:
    ConstrainedMap

    public final class ConstrainedMap.Transaction
extends Object
    This class allows to perform modification operations of this map on a snapshot that is created at the moment of construction of the transaction.

    Note that Transaction is not thread-safe and should be used in a single thread.

    Author:
    Fox Mulder

      • commit

        public void commit(boolean invalid)
        Completes the transaction. In other words, this method copies this snapshot values to the map.
        Parameters:
        invalid - Determines if this transaction should be committed anyway (even with invalid values).
        Throws:
        ViolationException - if this snapshot contains invalid values.

      • rollback

        public void rollback()
        Rolls back the transaction. In other words, this method copies current map values to this snapshot.
